Website: check out @user5. It looks easy, it works very well, and it's Open Source. I'm going to transfer one of my websites to it before the next renewal.
Signal: check out cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service with integrations for scheduling video calls with Element, Jitsi, etc. They also support Signal, but I haven't tested whether it's for messages or video.
I recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, Open Source.
